In [ ]:
def func(previous, now):
    if type(previous) == tuple:
        print(f'filter {previous[0]}: {len(final_main_info)} to {previous[1].sum()}')
        temp = np.logical_and(previous[1], now[1])
        print(f'filter {now[0]}: {previous[1].sum()} to {temp.sum()}')
        return temp
    else:
        temp = np.logical_and(previous, now[1])
        print(f'filter {now[0]}: {previous.sum()} to {temp.sum()}')
        return temp


filters_ = reduce(func, filters)

IV. Overall Performance¶

Return¶

$$ R_t^{real}=\frac{\left(NAV_t+Div_t\right)*SF_t}{NAV_{t-1}*SF_{t-1}}\tag{1} $$

$NAV_t$ $t$

$Div_t$ $t$

$SF_t$

$t$$s_t$, $SF_t=s_tSF_{t-1}$

$$ R_t^{real}=\frac{\left(NAV_t+Div_t\right)*s_t}{NAV_{t-1}}\tag{2} $$

def na_compare(row):
    date = row.name
    available_funds = row.dropna().index
    selected_share_info = (row * filled_share_info.loc[date]).dropna()
    available_share_funds = selected_share_info.index

    return [len(available_share_funds), len(available_funds)]

from factors import *

@fund_ended_check
@cache_wrapper(expire= 60 * 60 * 24 * 30)
def capm__generation(x):
    from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
    from data.TwoStepData.regression_source import regression_source
    x = x.dropna()
    temp_dates = x.index
    temp_regression = regression_source.loc[temp_dates]
     = LinearRegression().fit(X = temp_regression.mktrf.values.reshape(-1, 1), y = (x - temp_regression.rf).values).intercept_
    return 

all_fund_capm_ = return_of_all_fund_.loc[start_time: end_time].rolling(window = 36, min_periods = 36 - MAX_NA_NUM).parallel_apply(capm__generation)

from factors import *

@fund_ended_check
@cache_wrapper(expire= 60 * 60 * 24 * 30)
def svc__generation(x):
    from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
    from data.TwoStepData.regression_source import regression_source
    x = x.dropna()
    temp_dates = x.index
    temp_regression = regression_source.loc[temp_dates]
     = LinearRegression().fit(X = temp_regression[['mktrf', 'smb', 'vmg']].values, y = (x - temp_regression.rf).values).intercept_
    return

from factors import *

@fund_ended_check
@cache_wrapper(expire= 60 * 60 * 24 * 30)
def capm___generation(x):
    
    from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
    from data.TwoStepData.regression_source import regression_source
    import numpy as np
    x = x.dropna()
    temp_dates = x.index
    temp_regression = regression_source.loc[temp_dates]
    result = LinearRegression().fit(X = temp_regression.mktrf.values.reshape(-1, 1), y = (x - temp_regression.rf).values)
     = result.intercept_
     = (result.predict(temp_regression.mktrf.values.reshape(-1, 1)) - (x - temp_regression.rf).values).std()
    division =  / 

    if division < 1e3 and division > 1e-3:
        return division
    else:
        return np.nan

from data.TwoStepData.regression_source import regression_source

def wrapper_rolling_SVC(fund):
    def inner_rolling_SVC(return_data):
        co_time = np.intersect1d(return_data.index, regression_source.index)
        # rg_t - r_f =  + *mktrf + ...
        result = sm.OLS(return_data.loc[co_time] - regression_source.loc[co_time, 'rf'], regression_source.loc[co_time, ['', 'mktrf', 'smb', 'vmg']]).fit()
        return result.params[0]
    return fund.rolling(36).apply(inner_rolling_SVC)

rg__t = rg_t.apply(wrapper_rolling_SVC).dropna(how='all', axis=1).loc[start_time: end_time]

group_and_statistic(rg__t, groups=5, weighting='mkt', interval=1)
